{"TopicId":223613,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"are telescopes planned?","CreatedByName":"Kerbal410","CreatedById":212401,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-10T19:44:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal410","CreatedById":212401,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-10T19:44:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif space telescopes are coming, would it be more like the Sentinel, Spitzer, Euclid, Roman, Hubble, Webb, or Kepler? I know most of these are similar, but just want to get an idea of what to build if one comes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-02-10T19:45:02Z\u0022 title=\u002202/10/2024 07:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Feb 10\u0022\u003EFebruary 10\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbal410\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-10T21:24:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe plan was to have telescopes to discover planets around other stars. But where is that plan now, nobody knows. We\u0027ll find out in 0.4\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal410","CreatedById":212401,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-10T22:13:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224365732\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022223613\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221707600282\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n40 minutes ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe plan was to have telescopes to discover planets around other stars. But where is that plan now, nobody knows. We\u0027ll find out in 0.4\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat rules out the Sentinel I guess.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhas anything been said about surface scanning?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-10T22:59:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224365743\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022223613\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221707603199\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212401\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbal410\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, Kerbal410 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat rules out the Sentinel I guess.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wouldn\u0027t say that, asteroids are in the works as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224365743\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022223613\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221707603199\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212401\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbal410\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, Kerbal410 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhas anything been said about surface scanning?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe know of deep surface scanners for resources, judging by the size, ones you put on the ground, but I bet there will be some sort of recon part to get a rough data from orbit, like in KSP1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost of what\u0027s been said is in clickable TOTY2021 picture in my signature if you\u0027re looking for more info. Treat it with a spoon of salt because plans can change.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-02-10T22:59:26Z\u0022 title=\u002202/10/2024 10:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Feb 10\u0022\u003EFebruary 10\u003C/time\u003E by The Aziz\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"stephensmat","CreatedById":200752,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-10T23:11:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like a Space Telescope to unlock other systems. That\u0027s still a ways off, but it\u0027d be a way to keep the \u0027progression\u0027 that they\u0027re tying into missions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lowi_Sace","CreatedById":224820,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-14T12:42:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224365743\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022223613\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221707603199\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212401\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbal410\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/10/2024 at 11:13 PM, Kerbal410 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhas anything been said about surface scanning?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeining able to scan for recources and create temperature map (cooling colony) to determine were to build a base is very much needed. So I hope\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}